# Cloudflare Workers Local Development Variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your actual Google OAuth2 credentials
# This file is used by `wrangler dev` for local development

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE OAUTH2 CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# =============================================================================

# Google OAuth2 Client Credentials from Google Cloud Console
# Get these from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# Cookie encryption key for secure approval storage
# Generate a random 32+ character string for security
COOKIE_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-random-32-char-secret-key-here

# OAuth2 Redirect URI (must match exactly with Google Console)
# For local development with wrangler dev
REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8787/callback

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file: cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars
# 2. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com
# 3. Create a new project or select existing project
# 4. Enable Google Drive API and Google OAuth2 API
# 5. Go to Credentials â†’ Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 6. Choose "Web application"
# 7. Add authorized redirect URI: http://localhost:8787/callback
# 8. Copy Client ID and Client Secret to this file
# 9. If app is not published, add your email as a test user
# 10. Run: wrangler dev

# Security Notes:
# - This file is automatically ignored by git (.gitignore)
# - Never share these credentials
# - Client ID is not sensitive (visible in browser), but Client Secret is
# - For production, set these as Cloudflare Workers environment variables